Ninja 🥷 mode activated. Can you spot me? If you tilt your head and squint your eyes you just might find a wild Brook hanging amongst the deep terracotta entrada sandstone. 

right before this moment I stood peering over a 400 foot cliff as my friends counted down from 5 behind me. The sun setting and my heart racing.. 3.. 2.. 1..I leapt - screaming and smiling a big goofy grin as I met a new experience of gravity …even writing this, the all encompassing thrill it gave comes flooding back to my mind & body🤍 I’d then swing back and forth hundreds of feet in the air in disbelief, shouting at the top of my lungs, so in love with this life, surrounded by the sandstone giants, feeling so small yet so free.

 A 200 ft climb back the top awaited me as the sun challenged me to see just how quickly I could do it before the lights went out. 

My dad would question if I even love being alive to do something so crazy - but I’d argue these moments are the very thing that make me love it so much 🤍

looking back on 2022… what a beautiful year. Endless adventures, new friends, old friends, the fruition of dreams and years of seeds planted starting to sprout. To see things once only imagined begin to materialize. This year was honestly my first time starting to feel “older” - a feeling I’ve really loved, because it’s come with so many components I wish I could have given my younger self. A deeper realization that who I am is enough, even my ugliest, goofiest and most vulnerable states.  That there’s SO much beauty in honesty and raw authenticity. That it’s not “mean” to stand up for myself.🤍 That when I know who I am I don’t have to defend or crave others opinions. To tackle the hard things in life right away rather than throw them under the rug.

And a million more lessons but the main thing being that when you show up in life in a more conscious & intentional state you will attract others who are capable of that as well. And that has probably been the most exciting & deeply fulfilling adventure of all this past year. So I invite you on the adventure this next year to explore within. Sit with the things that hurt, analyze them, release them & grow. Ew I know does NOT sound like a fun adventure 🤣 but I can tell you from experience it leads to more joy & freedom than you could ever imagine. And it’s free too so that’s a bonus ;)

One of my favorite aspects of life has been watching things I never thought I’d like evolve into something I love. Growing up in small town South Carolina, I despised winter, counted down the days until spring and hated the overcast days of overwhelming shades of grey & brown. If you told little Brook that she’d be seeking out winter locations in the future she would have laughed so hard. Now I look for snowstorms and plan my trips around them.😂.. learning to embrace and lean in to mental shifts on how I view the world and things I love. We are an ever growing & evolving species, and that my friends is quite exciting.❄️

Happiness was never about following in the footsteps of all of those who came before you; it was never about being like the others. 🦋This being human is a guest house.
Every morning a new arrival.

A joy, a depression, a meanness,
some momentary awareness comes
As an unexpected visitor.

Welcome and entertain them all!
Even if they’re a crowd of sorrows,
who violently sweep your house
empty of its furniture,
still treat each guest honorably.
He may be clearing you out
for some new delight.

The dark thought, the shame, the malice,
meet them at the door laughing,
and invite them in.

Be grateful for whoever comes,
because each has been sent
as a guide from beyond.

— Jalaluddin Rumi, translation by Coleman Barks (The Essential Rumi)

Happy World Ocean Day 𓆉 I will forever be in awe of the world below. 

During my time in Moorea, I came across an incredible Non-Profit Organization called @coralgardeners  who have made it their mission to grow and plant resilient corals to restore dying reefs and bring life back to the ocean.

Together we can sponsor a nursery which is composed of 15 ropes with a few different species of corals, documented specifically by their fragmented location and species. Each nursery grows approximately 250 to 300 corals. 

I’ve attached a link in my bio to a Go Fund Me for the nursery. I would be honored and so excited if you would be interested in being apart of this journey and helping make a difference for our marine life and planet.

My favorite month of the year. (Might be bias because it’s birthday month hehe) but there’s just something so sweet about it. Even just the way it sounds rolling off the tongue is a tune that brings a different shade of joy. 

August, still summer time, full of freedom & endless sunshine but carries the reminder to savor every drop, because the next season anxiously awaits. 

August, a perfect time for a speed check. To reflect on the year so far and to dream of what you desire most for the last few remaining months. This very day, this very moment in our lives, will never quite look this way again. May we not wish it away. May we sit with it and feel it all. May this month bring you unique surprises, deep introspection, honesty, authenticity, healing, full circle moments and so so much joy.

Reading through my notes from a few months ago ♥︎ sometimes fun to share the deeper harder thoughts on here too:)

I’ve spent too many hours trying to wrap my my mind around the mishaps of life.. there’s the big ones that are so obviously out of our hands... but the small ones.. those are the ones that seem to refuse to vacate my mind. Our own human short comings, the unintentional ones, the friendships that no longer are, the intentions misinterpreted, the clashing of opinions too strong to mend with some we used to love most. It’s a wave of joy and sorrow in this existence and I’ve spent so much time wishing I had a magic wand that could just prevent anything but love. (I guess I am living up to my blonde Pagent girl stereotype of wishing for world peace) But I truly, to the depths of me, do. 

But alas, for some greater reason, that is not the way of this world. So until then, I will surrender. I will trust the flow of beautiful moments, people and places as they come and I will not cling to them. I will believe that though some chapters are shorter than others, they were all beautiful none the less🤍
